snippet.textDisplay: For me, to be honest, I do lie to my boyfriend in terms with my mental health and how I feel about situations  that makes me upset. In the past, when I talk about my mental health, it has always been invalidated and swept under the rug by people that I love. So because of that, it made me protect myself and trust myself to the point that i can't trust nobody. But obviously in a relationship, you have to have trust. So, learning that, at the start of the relationship was difficult because I felt like hes just going to invalidate me or that hes going to leave me because of it. It's hard for me to be vulnerable because I'm such a stubborn person and hardheaded and I act like I dont have feelings and I would try to be strong for him. But...talking to him, he was so understanding. He didn't invalidate me, he didn't judge me, he didn't make me feel uncomfortable for talking about it. He made me feel like I can talk about anything with him because he always remind me that were a team and that my problems are his problems and that we'll work it out together. Overtime, it made me more open, more outspoken, and just very comfortable on telling him anything. There are times where I still having that feeling of protecting myself and not letting him get affected because i want to deal with it on my own because I'm use to doing it myself. It's hard to really be vulnerable and admit that you need help. However, i had to remind myself that we are a team and that we will work it out together and that kinda helps me to be open again.
